S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureCatalogue.S100FC:name: Marine Aids to Navigation (AtoN)
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureCatalogue.S100FC:scope: Ocean, Coastal, Ports and Harbors. Excludes Inland waters.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Change Types
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Different categories or kinds of modifications that can be made to data, positions, or objects. For example, changes may involve updates to position, orientation, or attributes of an object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Based On Fixed Marks
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A straight route (known as a recommended track, range or leading line), which comprises: a. at least two structures (usually beacons or daymarks) and/or natural features, which may carry lights and/or top-marks. The structures/features are positioned so that when observed to be in line, a vessel can follow a known bearing with safety. (Adapted from International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA Aids to Navigation Guide, 1990); or b. a single structure or natural feature, which may carry lights and/or a topmark, and a specified bearing which can be followed with safety. (S-57 Edition 3.1, Appendix A Chapter 2, Page 2.72, November 2000, as amended).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Beacon Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the characteristic geometric form of the beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stake, Pole, Perch, Post
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An elongated wood or metal pole, driven into the ground or seabed, which serves as a navigational aid or a support for a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Withy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tree without roots stuck or spoiled into the bottom of the sea to serve as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid structure of the order of 10 metres in height used as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lattice Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure consisting of strips of metal or wood crossed or interlaced to form a structure to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pile Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A long heavy timber(s) or section(s) of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the seabed to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyant Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall spar-like beacon fitted with a permanently submerged buoyancy chamber, the lower end of the body is secured to seabed sinker either by a flexible joint or by a cable under tension.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Buoy Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The principal shape and/or design of a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Conical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has approximately the shape or the appearance of a pointed cone with the point upwards.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Can
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the shape of a cylinder, or a truncated cone that approximates to a cylinder, with a flat end uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spherical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shaped like a sphere, which is a body the surface of which is at all points equidistant from the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure is a narrow vertical structure, pillar or lattice tower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a pole, or of a very long cylinder, floating upright.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Barrel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a barrel or cylinder floating horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Superbuoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A very large buoy designed to carry a signal light of high luminous intensity at a high elevation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specially constructed shuttle shaped buoy which is used in ice conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Call Sign
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The designated call-sign of a station (radio station, radar station, pilot, ...).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Cardinal Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The four quadrants (north, east, south and west) are bounded by the true bearings NW-NE, NE-SE, SE-SW and SW-NW taken from the point of interest. A cardinal mark is named after the quadrant in which it is placed. The name of the cardinal mark indicates that it should be passed to the named side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NW-NE taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the north side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NE-SE taken from the point of interest. It should be passed to the east side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SE-SW taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the south side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SW-NW taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the west side of the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Fog Signal
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the various means of generating the fog signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Explosive
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal produced by the firing of explosive charges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diaphone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A diaphone uses compressed air and generally emits a powerful low-pitched sound, which often concludes with a brief sound of suddenly lowered pitch, termed the 'grunt'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Siren
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A type of fog signal apparatus which produces sound by virtue of the passage of air through slots or holes in a revolving disk.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautophone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A horn having a diaphragm oscillated by electricity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A reed uses compressed air and emits a weak, high pitched sound.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tyfon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A diaphragm horn which operates under the influence of compressed air or steam.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bell
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A ringing sound with a short range.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Whistle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A distinctive sound made by a jet of air passing through an orifice. The apparatus may be operated automatically, by hand or by air being forced up a tube by waves acting on a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gong
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A sound produced by vibration of a disc when struck.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A horn uses compressed air or electricity to vibrate a diaphragm and exists in a variety of types which differ greatly in their sound and power.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Installation Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of fixed installation buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Catenary Anchor Leg Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Incorporates a large buoy which remains on the surface at all times and is moored by 4 or more anchors. Mooring hawsers and cargo hoses lead from a turntable on top of the buoy, so that the buoy does not turn as the ship swings to wind and stream.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Single Buoy Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large mooring buoy used by tankers to load and unload in port approaches or in offshore oil and gas fields.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Landmark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of prominent cultural and natural features in the landscape.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cemetery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A site and associated structures devoted to the burial of the dead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chimney
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical structure containing a passage or flue for discharging smoke and gases of combustion.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dish Aerial
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A parabolic aerial for the receipt and transmission of high frequency radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flagstaff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A staff or pole on which flags are raised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flare Stack
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall structure used for burning-off waste oil or gas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A relatively tall structure usually held vertical by guy lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windsock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tapered fabric sleeve mounted so as to catch and swing with the wind, thus indicating the wind direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Monument
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure erected and/or maintained as a memorial to a person and/or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Column/Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cylindrical or slightly tapering body of considerably greater length than diameter erected vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Memorial Plaque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A slab of metal, usually ornamented, erected as a memorial to a person or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Obelisk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tapering shaft usually of stone or concrete, square or rectangular in section, with a pyramidal apex.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Statue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A representation of a living being, sculptured, moulded, or cast in a variety of materials (for example: marble, metal, or plaster).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cross
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A monument, or other structure in form of a cross.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dome
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A landmark comprising a hemispherical or spheroidal shaped structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radar Scanner
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A device used for directing a radar beam through a search pattern.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A relatively tall, narrow structure that may either stand alone or may form part of another structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windmill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of vanes attached to a tower and driven by wind (excluding wind turbines).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spire/Minaret
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall conical or pyramid-shaped structure often built on the roof or tower of a building, especially a church or mosque.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Large Rock or Boulder on Land
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An isolated rocky formation or a single large stone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangulation Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A recoverable point on the earth, whose geographic position has been determined by angular methods with geodetic instruments. A triangulation point is a selected point, which has been marked with a station mark, or it is a conspicuous natural or artificial feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boundary Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A marker identifying the location of a surveyed boundary line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation Wheel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wheels with passenger cars mounted external to the rim and independently rotated by electric motors.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Torii
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A form of decorative gateway or portal, consisting of two upright wooden posts connected at the top by two horizontal crosspieces, commonly found at the entrance to Shinto temples.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure erected over a depression or an obstacle such as a body of water, railroad, etc., to provide a roadway for vehicles or pedestrians.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A barrier to check or confine anything in motion; particularly one constructed to hold back water and raise its level to form a reservoir, or to prevent flooding.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Lateral Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of lateral marks in the IALA Buoyage System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port-Hand Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard-Hand Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Starboard Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage", the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Port Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage", the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of different light types.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light associated with other lights so as to form a leading line to be followed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aero Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An aero light is established for aeronautical navigation and may be of higher power than marine lights and visible from well offshore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flood Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A broad beam light used to illuminate a structure or area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strip Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light whose source has a linear form generally horizontal, which can reach a length of several metres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Subsidiary Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light placed on or near the support of a main light and having a special use in navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spotlight
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A powerful light focused so as to illuminate a small area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Front
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upper
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Emergency
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light available as a backup to a main light which will be illuminated should the main light fail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bearing Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which enables its approximate bearing to be obtained without the use of a compass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horizontally Disposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A group of lights of identical character and almost identical position, that are disposed horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertically Disposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A group of lights of identical character and almost identical position, that are disposed vertically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radar transponder beacon based on functionality.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ramark, Radar Beacon Transmitting Continuously
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar marker beacon which continuously transmits a signal appearing as a radial line on a radar screen, the line indicating the direction of the beacon. Ramarks are intended primarily for marine use. The name 'ramark' is derived from the words radar marker.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Racon, Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar beacon which returns a coded signal which provides identification of the beacon, as well as range and bearing. The range and bearing are indicated by the location of the first character received on the radar screen. The name 'racon' is derived from the words radar beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Racon/Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar beacon that may be used (in conjunction with at least one other radar beacon) to indicate a leading line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Schedule
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of schedule, for instance opening, closure, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Normal Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service, office, is open, fully manned, and operating normally, or the area is accessible as usual.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Closure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service, office, or area is closed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unmanned Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service is available but not manned.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Special Purpose Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an aid to navigation which signifies some special purpose.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Firing Danger Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a firing danger area, usually at sea.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Target Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any object toward which something is directed. The distinctive marking or instrumentation of a ground point to aid its identification on a photograph.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marker Ship Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark marking the position of a ship which is used as a target during some military exercise.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Degaussing Range Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a degaussing range.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Barge Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark of relevance to barges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cable Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the position of submarine cables or the point at which they run on to the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spoil Ground Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the limit of a spoil ground.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Outfall Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the position of an outfall or the point at which it leaves the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ODAS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Ocean Data Acquisition System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recording Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to record data for scientific purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seaplane Anchorage Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a seaplane anchorage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recreation Zone Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a recreation zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mooring Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a mooring or moorings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: LANBY
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large buoy designed to take the place of a lightship where construction of an offshore light station is not feasible.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Aids to navigation or other indicators so located as to indicate the path to be followed. Leading marks identify a leading line when they are in transit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Measured Distance Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark forming part of a transit indicating one end of a measured distance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Notice Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A notice board or sign indicating information to the mariner.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: TSS Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a Traffic Separation Scheme.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchoring Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an anchoring prohibited area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Berthing Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that berthing is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Overtaking Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that overtaking is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Two-Way Traffic Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a one-way route.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reduced Wake Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that vessels must not generate excessive wake.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Speed Limit Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a speed limit applies.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stop Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the place where the bow of a ship must stop when traffic lights show red.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: General Warning Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that special caution must be exercised in the vicinity of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sound Ship's Siren Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a ship should sound its siren or horn.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Restricted Vertical Clearance Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the minimum vertical space available for passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maximum Vessel's Draught Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the maximum draught of vessel permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Restricted Horizontal Clearance Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the minimum horizontal space available for passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strong Current Warning Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark warning of strong currents.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Berthing Permitted Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that berthing is allowed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Overhead Power Cable Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an overhead power cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Channel Edge Gradient Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the gradient of the slope of a dredge channel edge.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telephone Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the presence of a telephone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ferry Crossing Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a ferry route crosses the ship route; often used with a 'sound ship's siren' mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pipeline Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the position of submarine pipelines or the point at which they run on to the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchorage Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an anchorage area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clearing Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a clearing line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Control Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the location at which a restriction or requirement exists.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diving Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that diving may take place in the vicinity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Refuge Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark providing or indicating a place of safety.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Foul Ground Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a foul ground.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yachting Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark installed for use by yachtsmen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Heliport Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an area where helicopters may land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GNSS Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a location at which a GNSS position has been accurately determined.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seaplane Landing Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an area where seaplanes land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that entry is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Work in Progress Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that work (generally construction) is in progress.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mark With Unknown Purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark whose detailed characteristics are unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wellhead Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a borehole that produces or is capable of producing oil or natural gas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Channel Separation Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the point at which a channel divides separately into two channels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marine Farm Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the existence of a fish, mussel, oyster or pearl farm/culture.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Artificial Reef Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the existence or the extent of an artificial reef.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark, used year round, that may be submerged when ice passes through the area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nature Reserve Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to define the boundary of a nature reserve.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Aggregating Device
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A fish aggregating (or aggregation) device (FAD) is a man-made object used to attract ocean going pelagic fish such as marlin, tuna and mahi-mahi (dolphin fish). They usually consist of buoys or floats tethered to the ocean floor with concrete blocks or adrift.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wreck Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a wreck.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a customs checkpoint.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Causeway Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a causeway.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wave Recorder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A surface following buoy used to measure wave activity.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Zone of Confidence In Data
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the zone of confidence in data within an area based on the positional accuracy, survey equipment and coverage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence A1
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 5 metres + 5% depth; Depth Accuracy 0.5 metre + 1% depth; Full area search undertaken. Significant seafloor features detected and depths measured; Controlled, systematic survey, high position and depth accuracy achieved using DGPS or a minimum three high quality lines of position (LOP) and a multibeam, channel or mechanical sweep system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence A2
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 20 metres; Depth Accuracy 1.0 metre + 2% depth; Full area search undertaken. Significant seafloor features detected and depths measured; Controlled, systematic survey achieving position and depth accuracy less than ZOC A1 and using a modern survey echosounder and a sonar or mechanical sweep system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 50 metres; Depth Accuracy 1.0 metre + 2% depth; Full area search not achieved, uncharted features hazardous to surface navigation are not expected but may exist; Controlled, systematic survey achieving similar depth but lesser position accuracies than ZOCA2, using a modern survey echosounder, but no sonar or mechanical sweep system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence C
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 500 metres; Depth Accuracy 2.0 metre + 5% depth; Full area search not achieved, depth anomalies may be expected; Low accuracy survey or data collected on an opportunity basis such as soundings on passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence D
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy worse than ZOC C; Depth Accuracy worse than ZOC C; Full area search not achieved, large depth anomalies may be expected; Poor quality data or data that cannot be quality assessed due to lack of information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence U
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quality of the bathymetric data has yet to be assessed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The property possessed by an object of producing different sensations on the eye as a result of the way it reflects or emits light.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour Pattern
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A regular repeated design containing more than one colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horizontal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertical Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diagonal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented diagonally (that is, not horizontally or vertically).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Squared
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Often referred to as checker plate, where alternate colours are used to create squares similar to a chess or draught board. The pattern may be straight or diagonal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stripes (Direction Unknown)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented in an unknown direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Border Stripe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A band or stripe of colour which is displayed around the outer edge of the feature, which may also form a border to an inner pattern or plain colour.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Communication Channel
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A channel number assigned to a specific radio frequency, frequencies or frequency band.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Condition
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various conditions of buildings and other constructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Being built but not yet capable of function.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ruined
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure in a decayed or deteriorated condition resulting from neglect or disuse, or a damaged structure in need of repair.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Reclamation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of the sea, a lake or the navigable part of a river that is being reclaimed as land, usually by the dumping of earth and other material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wingless
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A windmill or wind turbine from which the vanes or turbine blades are missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Planned Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Detailed planning has been completed but construction has not been initiated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Instructions
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Instructions provided on how to contact a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Disused
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that an entity ceases to be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date of an event.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Variable
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A day which is not fixed in the Gregorian calendar.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Any one of seven days in a week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sunday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Saturday and preceding Monday.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Monday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Sunday and preceding Tuesday.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tuesday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Monday and preceding Wednesday.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wednesday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Tuesday and preceding Thursday.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Thursday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Wednesday and preceding Friday.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Friday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Thursday and preceding Saturday.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Saturday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The day of the week following Friday and preceding Sunday.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Day of Week is Range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if the days of the week identified define a range or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Default Clearance Depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth value determined for an underwater hazard of unknown depth, based on the depth of the surrounding area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth Range Maximum Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum (deepest) value of a depth range.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth Range Minimum Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum (shoalest) value of a depth range.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Destination
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The place or general direction to which a vessel is going or directed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Distance Mark Visible
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement indicating whether a distance mark is visible or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Distance Unit of Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A specified amount of a quantity, as of length, by comparison with which any other quantity of the same kind is measured or estimated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The basic unit of length in the International System of Units (SI) system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yards
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A common unit of linear measure in English-speaking countries, equal to 3 feet or 36 inches, and equivalent to 0.9144 metre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Kilometres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of length, the common measure of distances equal to 1000 metres, and equivalent to 3280.8 feet or 0.621 mile.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Statute Miles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit equal to 5280 feet.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautical Miles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of length equal to 1,852 metres. This value was approved by the International Hydrographic Conference of 1929 and has been adopted by nearly all maritime states.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Dredged Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that dredging occurred.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Elevation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The altitude of the ground level of a feature, measured from a specified vertical datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Estimated Range of Transmission
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The estimated range of a non-optical electromagnetic transmission.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Exhibition Condition of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The outward display of the light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Light Shown Without Change of Character
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light shown throughout the 24 hours without change of character.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Daytime Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which is only exhibited by day.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fog Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which is exhibited in fog or conditions of reduced visibility.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Night Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which is only exhibited at night.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Flare Bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The bearing about which the light flare symbol is rotated to be displayed in ECDIS.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Flare Stack
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A tall structure used for burning-off waste oil or gas.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Frequency Shore Station Receives
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shore station receiver frequency.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Frequency Shore Station Transmits
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shore station transmitter frequency.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Drawing Index
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A numeric value used to indicate that datasets are intended to form a seamless presentation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Full Seafloor Coverage Achieved
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Expression stating if full seafloor coverage has been achieved in the area covered by hydrographic surveys.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Function
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A specific role that describes a feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Harbour-Masters Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A local official who has charge of mooring and berthing of vessels, collecting harbour fees, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Serves as a government office where customs duties are collected, the flow of goods are regulated and restrictions enforced, and shipments or vehicles are cleared for entering or leaving a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Health Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The office which is charged with the administration of health laws and sanitary inspections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hospital
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An institution or establishment providing medical or surgical treatment for the ill or wounded.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Post Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The public department, agency or organisation responsible primarily for the collection, transmission and distribution of mail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hotel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An establishment, especially of a comfortable or luxurious kind, where paying visitors are provided with accommodation, meals and other services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Railway Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building with platforms where trains arrive, load, discharge and depart.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Police Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The headquarters of a local police force and that is where those under arrest are first charged.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water-Police Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The headquarters of a local water-police force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The office or headquarters of pilots; the place where the services of a pilot may be obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A distinctive structure or place on shore from which personnel keep watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bank Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An office for custody, deposit, loan, exchange or issue of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Headquarters for District Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quarters of an executive officer (director, manager, etc.) with responsibility for an administrative area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Transit Shed/Warehouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or part of a building for storage of wares or goods.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Factory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or buildings with equipment for manufacturing; a workshop.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Power Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A stationary plant containing apparatus for large scale conversion of some form of energy (such as hydraulic, steam, chemical or nuclear energy) into electrical energy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Administrative
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for the management of affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Educational Facility
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An establishment for teaching and learning (for example school, college, university, etc).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Church
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Christian worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chapel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place for Christian worship other than a parish, cathedral or church, especially one attached to a private house or institution.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Jewish worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pagoda
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A Hindu or Buddhist temple or sacred building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shinto Shrine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Shinto worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buddhist Temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Buddhist worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mosque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A Muslim place of worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marabout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A shrine marking the burial place of a Muslim holy man.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Keeping a watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Communication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmitting and/or receiving electronic communication signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Television
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system for reproducing on a screen visual images transmitted (usually with sound) by radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmitting and/or receiving radio-frequency electromagnetic waves as a means of communication.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A method, system or technique of using beamed, reflected, and timed radio waves for detecting, locating, or tracking objects, and for measuring altitudes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Light Support
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure serving as a support for one or more lights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Microwave
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Broadcasting and receiving signals using microwaves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cooling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Generation of chilled liquid and/or gas for cooling purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place from which the surroundings can be observed but at which a watch is not habitually maintained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timeball
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A visual time signal in the form of a ball.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Instrument for measuring time and recording hours.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used to control the flow of traffic within a specified range of an installation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Airship Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Equipment or structure to secure an airship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stadium
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arena for holding and viewing events.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bus Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building where buses and coaches regularly stop to take on and/or let off passengers, especially for long-distance travel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Rescue Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit responsible for promoting efficient organization of search and rescue services and for coordinating the conduct of search and rescue operations within a search and rescue region.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building designed and equipped for making observations of astronomical, meteorological, or other natural phenomena.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore Crusher
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or structure used to crush ore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boathouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or shed, usually built partly over water, for sheltering a boat or boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pumping Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A facility to move solids, liquids or gases by means of pressure or suction.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the feature, measured from a specified vertical datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length of a feature, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical length of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The physical horizontal clearance distance between two points on a feature, such as a bridge span, dock, gate, lock or tunnel.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The width of a feature, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical width of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Distance Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the horizontal accuracy of horizontal clearances and distances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the longer of two linear axis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the shorter of two linear axis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Ice Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the maximum variation in the vertical clearance of an overhead cable due to an accumulation of ice.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: IMO Adopted
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A defined maritime traffic route that has been adopted as an IMO routeing measure.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: In Dispute
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if an area is in a jurisdictional dispute.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Interoperability Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A common unique identifier for entities which describe a single real-world feature, and which is used to identify instances of the feature in end-user systems where the feature may be included in multiple data product types.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: In the Water
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication if the feature is located in or over navigable water.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Is MRCC
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if a Coast Guard station performs the function of a Maritime Rescue and Coordination Centre.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Least Depth of Detected Features Measured
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Expression stating if the least depth of detected features in an area was measured.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Lifting Capacity
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific safe lifting capacity of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Light Characteristic
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distinct character, such as fixed, flashing, or occulting, which is given to each light to avoid confusion with neighbouring ones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, with constant luminous intensity and colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 50 flashes per minutes but less than 80 flashes per minutes. It may be: - Continuous quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated. - Group quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 80 flashes per minute but less than 160 flashes per minute. It may be:- Continuous very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated.- Group very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Continuous Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are regularly repeated at a rate of not less than 160 flashes per minute.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isophased
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light with all durations of light and darkness equal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and all the eclipses are of equal duration. It may be: - Single-occulting: An occulting light in which an eclipse is regularly repeated. - Group-occulting: An occulting light in which a group of two or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated. - Composite group-occulting: An occulting light in which a sequence of groups of one or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated, and the groups comprise different numbers of eclipses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Interrupted Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in which the ultra quick flashes (160 or more per minute) are interrupted at regular intervals by eclipses of long duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Morse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which appearances of light of two clearly different durations are grouped to represent a character or characters in the Morse code.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a flashing light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which an occulting light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating light in which the total duration of light in each period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and in which the intervals of darkness (occultations) are all of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of very quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ultra Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of ultra quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, two or more colours in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Alternating Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity and different colour.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Light Visibility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific visibility of a light, with respect to the light's intensity and ease of recognition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Intensity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Non-marine lights with a higher power than marine lights and visible from well off shore (often 'Aero' lights).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Intensity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Non-marine lights with lower power than marine lights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Faint
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A decrease in the apparent intensity of a light which may occur in the case of partial obstructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Intensified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in a sector is intensified (that is, has longer range than other sectors).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unintensified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in a sector is unintensified (that is, has shorter range than other sectors).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visibility Deliberately Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light sector is deliberately reduced in intensity, for example to reduce its effect on a built-up area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Said of the arc of a light sector designated by its limiting bearings in which the light is not visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Partially Obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This value specifies that parts of the sector are obscured.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visible in Line of Range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lights that must be in line to be visible.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Line Spacing Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum distance between hydrographic survey lines.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Line Spacing Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum distance between hydrographic survey lines.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Linkage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Location (address) for online access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Magnetic Anomaly Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the deviation from the normal magnetic variation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Direction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A direction used as a basis for comparison of other directions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Major Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a light is considered to be a major light in terms of ECDIS display in a particular area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marks Navigational - System Of
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: no system
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: main European inland waterway marking system
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids as required in international, national or regional regulations that contain the same navigational aids as the European Code for Inland Waterways of UNECE, or if there is no regulation for a waterway, navigational aids as recommended in the European Code for Inland Waterways of UNECE.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value considered by the Data Producer to be the maximum (largest) scale at which the data is to be displayed before it can be considered to be "grossly overscaled".

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Permitted Draught
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum draught of a vessel permitted along a route, in a channel or dock, at a berth, or over a submerged feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Permitted Vessel Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum length of a vessel permitted in a channel or dock, at a berth, or at an anchorage or mooring.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Measured Distance
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A course at sea, whose ends are indicated by ranges ashore, and whose length has been accurately measured for determining the speed of vessels.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Measurement Distance Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum spacing of the principal measurement lines of a hydrographic survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Measurement Distance Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum spacing of the principal measurement lines of a hydrographic survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: MMSI Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The Maritime Mobile Service Identity (MMSI) Code is formed of a series of nine digits which are transmitted over the radio path in order to uniquely identify ship stations, ship earth stations, coast stations, coast earth stations, and group calls. These identities are formed in such a way that the identity or part thereof can be used by telephone and telex subscribers connected to the general telecommunications network principally to call ships automatically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Moire Effect
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A short range (up to 2km) type of directional light. Sodium lighting gives a yellow background to a screen on which a vertical black line will be seen by an observer on the centre line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Multiplicity Known
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group is or is not known.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name of Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the online resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name Usage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the type and display level of the name of a feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Default Name Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name is intended to be displayed when the end-user system is set to the default name/text display setting.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternate Name Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name is intended to be displayed when the end-user system is set to an alternate name/text display setting, for example an alternate language.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nationality
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier of membership of a particular nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Construction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The building's primary construction material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Masonry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of stones or bricks, usually quarried, shaped, and mortared.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Concreted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of concrete, a material made of sand and gravel that is united by cement into a hardened mass used for roads, foundations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Loose Boulders
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from large stones or blocks of concrete, often placed loosely for protection against waves or water turbulence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hard Surfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with a surface of hard material, usually a term applied to roads surfaced with asphalt or concrete.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unsurfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with no extra protection, usually a term applied to roads not surfaced with a hard material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wooden
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from wood.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass Reinforced Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from a plastic material strengthened with fibres of glass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Latticed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure of crossed wooden or metal strips usually arranged to form a diagonal pattern of open spaces between the strips.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: [1] Any artificial or natural substance having similar properties and composition, as fused borax, obsidian, or the like. [2] Something made of such a substance, as a windowpane.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Surface
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The general material which the land surface or the seabed is composed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mud
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Soft, wet earth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Silt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An unconsolidated sediment whose particles range in size from 0.0039 to 0.0625 millimetres in diameter (between clay and sand size).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gravel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of 2.0 - 4.0mm); small stones with coarse sand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pebbles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small stone worn smooth and rounded by the action of water, sand, ice, etc. ranging in diameter between 4 and 64 millimetres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cobbles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A naturally rounded stone larger than a pebble.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any formation of natural origin that constitutes an integral part of the lithosphere. The natural occurring material that forms firm, hard, and solid masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lava
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fluid or semi-fluid matter flowing from a volcano. The substance that results from the cooling of the molten rock. Part of the ocean bed is composed of lava.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hard calcareous skeletons of many tribes of marine polyps.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shells
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The hard outside covering of an animal. Part of the ocean bed is composed of numerous shells of marine animals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boulder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rounded rock with diameter of 256 millimetres or larger.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Surface - Qualifying Terms
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The nature of various forms of natural surface materials in terms of their size, morphology and consistency.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Falls within the smallest size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Medium
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Falls within the moderate size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coarse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Falls within the largest size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Broken
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Fractured or in pieces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sticky
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having an adhesive or glue like property.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Soft
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not hard or firm.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stiff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not pliant; thick, resistant to flow.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Volcanic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Composed of or containing material ejected from a volcano.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Calcareous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Composed of or containing calcium or calcium carbonate.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Firm; usually refers to an area of the seafloor not covered by unconsolidated sediment.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Number of Features
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Opening Bridge
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A bridge that is closed when set for carrying road traffic and open when set to permit marine traffic to pass through the waterway it crosses. Modern opening (movable) bridges are either bascule, vertical lift or swing.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a bearing.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pictorial Representation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced picture file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Product
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various substances which are transported, stored or exploited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Oil
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A thick, slippery liquid that will not dissolve in water, usually petroleum based in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance with particles that can move freely, usually a fuel substance in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A colourless, odourless, tasteless liquid that is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A hard black mineral that is burned as fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid rock or mineral from which metal is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chemicals
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any substance obtained by or used in a chemical process.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drinking Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Water that is suitable for human consumption.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Milk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A white fluid secreted by female mammals as food for their young.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bauxite
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mineral from which aluminum is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coke
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid substance obtained after gas and tar have been extracted from coal, used as a fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Iron Ingots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An oblong lump of cast iron metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Salt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Sodium chloride obtained from mines or by the evaporation of sea water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wood prepared for use in building or carpentry.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sawdust/Wood Chips
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Powdery fragments of wood made in sawing timber or coarse chips produced for use in manufacturing pressed board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scrap Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Discarded metal suitable for being reprocessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Natural Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Natural gas that has been liquefied for ease of transport by cooling the gas to -162 Celsius.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Petroleum Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A compressed gas consisting of flammable light hydrocarbons and derived from petroleum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fermented juice of grapes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance made of powdered lime and clay, mixed with water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small hard seed, especially that of any cereal plant such as wheat, rice, corn, rye etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Electricity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electric charge or current.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The solid form of water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of Horizontal Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The degree of reliability attributed to a position.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A position that is considered to be less than third-order accuracy, but is generally considered to be within 30.5 metres of its correct geographic location. Also may apply to a feature whose position does not remain fixed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Band
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The band code character of the electromagnetic spectrum within which radar wave lengths lie.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Conspicuous
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A feature which returns a strong radar echo.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radius
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vector extending from the centre to the periphery of a circular or spherical feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Location
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information relating to the point of origin for a measured distance as indicated on a distance mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Tide
