S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference tide to which the series of tidal stream values apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Tide Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of tide range (that is, mean spring tide, mean neap tide or mean tide) for which a set of tidal stream rates and directions apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The tides of increased range occurring near the times of full moon and new moon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Neaps
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The tides of decreased range occurring near the times of first and last quarter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The tides of mean range occurring between spring and neap tides.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Year for Magnetic Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference calendar year for magnetic variation values.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Regulation Citation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The regulation citation for a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reported Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that the item was observed, done, or investigated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Value Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The largest scale for the range of survey scale.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Value Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest scale for the range of survey scale.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector bearing specifies the limit of the sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Arc Extension
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication that the default radius of a sector arc is to be extended by 5mm.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Line Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector line length specifies the displayed length of the line, in ground units, defining the limit of the sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Duration
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time occupied by a single instance of light/sound or eclipse/silence in a signal sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Frequency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The frequency of a signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Generation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The mechanism used to generate a fog or light signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Automatically
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Signal generation is initiated by a self regulating mechanism such as a timer or light sensor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: By Wave Action
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The signal is generated by the motion of the sea surface such as a bell in a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: By Hand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The signal is generated by a manually operated mechanism such as a hand cranked siren.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: By Wind
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The signal is generated by the motion of air such as a wind driven whistle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio Activated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Activated by radio signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Call Activated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Activated by making a call to a manned station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Group
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of signals, the combination of signals or the morse character(s) within one period of full sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Period
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time occupied by an entire cycle of intervals of light and eclipse.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of light/sound or eclipse/silence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lit/Sound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of light or sound.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Eclipsed/Silent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of eclipse or silence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Significant Features Detected
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if significant features have or have not been detected in the course of a survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Size of Features Detected
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The size of detected bathymetric features in an area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The publication, document, or reference work from which information comes or is acquired.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed Limit
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum allowed rate of travel in an area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Rate of motion. The terms speed and velocity are often used interchangeably, but speed is a scalar, having magnitude only, while velocity is a vector quantity, having both magnitude and direction. Speed maximum is the maximum rate of travel that can occur.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Rate of motion. The terms speed and velocity are often used interchangeably, but speed is a scalar, having magnitude only, while velocity is a vector quantity, having both magnitude and direction. Speed minimum is the minimum rate of travel that can occur.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed Units
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The units for description of speed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Kilometres Per Hour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of speed, expressing the number of kilometres travelled in one hour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Miles Per Hour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An imperial and United States customary unit of speed expressing the number of statute miles covered in one hour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Knots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A nautical unit of speed. One knot is one nautical mile per hour. The name is derived from the knots in the log line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Station Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of the reference tide station with reference water level for tidal stream panel observations.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Station Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The identification number of the reference tide station with reference water level for tidal stream panel observations.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acting on special occasions; happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Presented as worthy of confidence, acceptance, use, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not in Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Use has ceased, but the facility still exists intact; disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Periodic/Intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Recurring at intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reserved
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Set apart for some specific use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Administered by an individual or corporation, rather than a State or a public body.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mandatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Compulsory; enforced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extinguished
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No longer lit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Illuminated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lit by flood lights, strip lights, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Famous in history; of historical interest.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Public
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Belonging to, available to, used or shared by, the community as a whole and not restricted to private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synchronized
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occur at a time, coincide in point of time, be contemporary or simultaneous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Looked at or observed over a period of time especially so as to be aware of any movement or change.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unwatched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually automatic in operation, without any permanently-stationed personnel to superintend it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Existence Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A feature that has been reported but has not been definitely determined to exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Marked by buoys.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Stream Depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth below the sea surface to which the tidal stream data refers relative to the sounding datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Surrounding Depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth value determined for seabed around an underwater hazard, based on the depth of the surrounding area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Survey Authority
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The authority which was responsible for the survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Update Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Update number of the ENC being referenced.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Swept Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that the area was swept by a survey.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An identifier, such as words, numbers, letters, symbols, or any combination of those used to establish a contact to a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Service
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of methods of communication over a distance by electrical, electronic, or electromagnetic means.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Voice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The transfer or exchange of information by using sounds that are being made by mouth and throat when speaking.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Facsimile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of transmitting and reproducing graphic matter (as printing or still pictures) by means of signals sent over telephone lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: SMS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Short Message Service is a form of text messaging communication on phones and mobile phones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A representation of facts, concepts or instructions in a formalised manner suitable for communication, interpretation or processing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Streamed Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data that is constantly received by and presented to an end-user while being delivered by a provider.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telex
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of communication in which messages are sent over long distances by using a telephone system and are printed by using a special machine (called a teletypewriter).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telegraph
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An apparatus, system or process for communication at a distance by electric transmission over wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Email
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Messages and other data exchanged between individuals using computers in a network.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Offset Bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north that text associated with a feature is positioned from the feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Offset Distance
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distance that text associated with a feature is positioned from the feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Rotation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if text associated with a feature is to be rotated in the ECDIS display or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the end of an active period.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the start of an active period.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time Relative to Tide
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time difference relative to the reference tide.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Topmark/Daymark Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shape a topmark or daymark exhibits.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cone (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Is where the vertex points up.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cone (Point Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Is where the vertex points down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sphere
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A curved surface all points of which are equidistant from a fixed point within, called the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Spheres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Two spheres, one above the other. Two black spheres are commonly used as an International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmark (isolated danger).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cylinder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid geometrical figure generated by straight lines fixed in direction and describing with one of point a closed curve, especially a circle (in which case the figure is circular cylinder, its ends being parallel circles).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Board
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually of rectangular shape, made from timber or metal and used to provide a contrast with the natural background of a daymark. The actual daymark is often painted on to this board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: X-Shaped
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having a shape or a cross-section like the capital letter X.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upright Cross
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cross with one vertical member and one horizontal member; that is, similar in shape to the character '+'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cube (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cube standing on one of its vertexes. A cube is a solid contained by six equal squares, a regular hexahedron.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Point to Point)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices together in the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Base to Base)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their bases together in the centre and their vertices pointing up and down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rhombus
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A plane figure having four equal sides and equal opposite angles (two acute and two obtuse); an oblique equilateral parallelogram.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Points Upward)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices pointing up.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Points Downward)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices pointing down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Besom (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A bundle of rods or twigs. A besom, point up is where the thicker (untied) end of the besom is at the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Besom (Point Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A bundle of rods or twigs. A besom, point down is where the thinner (tied) end of the besom is at the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flag
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A flag mounted on a short pole.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sphere Over a Rhombus
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A sphere located above a rhombus.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Square
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A plane figure with four right angles and four equal straight sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle (Horizontal)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A horizontal rectangle is where the two longer opposite sides are standing horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle (Vertical)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical rectangle is where the two longer opposite sides are standing vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trapezium (Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quadrilateral having one pair of opposite sides parallel, and which stands on its longer parallel side.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trapezium (Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quadrilateral having one pair of opposite sides parallel, and which stands on its shorter parallel side.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A figure having three angles and three sides, and which has a vertex at the top.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle (Point Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A figure having three angles and three sides, and which has a side at the top.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A perfectly round plane figure whose circumference is everywhere equidistant from its centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Two Upright Crosses (One Over the Other)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Two upright crosses, generally vertically disposed one above the other.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: T-Shape
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having a shape like the capital letter T.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle Pointing Up Over a Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A triangle, vertex uppermost, located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upright Cross Over a Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An upright cross located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rhombus Over a Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhombus located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Circle Over a Triangle Pointing Up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A circle located over a triangle, vertex uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other Shape (See Shape Information)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An uncommon and/or non-standardized shape as textually described using an associated attribute.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Variable Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The factor to be applied to the variable component of an uncertainty equation so as to provide the best estimate of the variable horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Underlying Layer
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The position of the seabed type within the layers of the seabed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Annual Change in Magnetic Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The annual change in magnetic variation values.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Depth Contour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth of a sea bottom contour.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Magnetic Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angle between the magnetic and geographical meridians at any place, expressed in degrees east or west to indicate the direction of magnetic north from true north.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Maximum Range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extreme distance at which a feature can be seen or a signal detected.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Nominal Range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The luminous range of a light in a homogenous atmosphere in which the meteorological visibility is 10 sea miles.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Sounding
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the measurement of a sounding relative to the chart datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Unlimited
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if the vertical clearance for a feature in the open position, such as a bridge span, is unlimited.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the low waters of spring tides. This level is used as a tidal datum in some areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or somewhat lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water Springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides. It was first used in waters surrounding India.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Lowest Astronomical Tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian Spring Low Water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Lower Low Water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the high waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Sea Level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Higher High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equinoctial Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-Père, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower Low Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Highest High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The datum refers to each Baltic country's realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The total vertical length of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vessel Class
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The classification of a vessel, normally as defined by length or gross tonnage.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Virtual AIS Aid to Navigation Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A purpose of a virtual AIS Aid to Navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the north side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the east side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the south side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the west side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Lateral (IALA A)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the “conventional direction of buoyage” in the IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard Lateral (IALA A)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the “conventional direction of buoyage” in the IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Lateral (IALA B)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the “conventional direction of buoyage” in the IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard Lateral (IALA B)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the “conventional direction of buoyage” in the IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isolated Danger
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used alone to indicate a dangerous reef or shoal. The mark may be passed on either hand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Safe Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Special Purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special purpose aid is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notice to Mariners.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Emergency Wreck Marking
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a recent wreck.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visitors Mooring
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A mooring set aside for the use of visiting vessels.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visual Prominence
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extent to which a feature, either natural or artificial, is visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term applied to an object either natural or artificial which is distinctly and notably visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An object that may be visible from seaward, but cannot be used as a fixing mark and is not conspicuous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Prominent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Objects which are easily identifiable, but do not justify being classed as conspicuous.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Waterway Distance
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length of the space between two points along a waterway.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Wave Length Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distance between two successive peaks (or other points of identical phase) on an electromagnetic wave.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Berth Depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The least depth of the body of water at the berth or in a berth pocket adjacent to the berth.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Optimum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The largest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Drawing Instruction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Text describing one or more graphic elements that must be rendered in an end-user system.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Directional Character
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A directional light is a light illuminating a sector of very narrow angle and intended to mark a direction to follow.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Fixed Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: An active period of a single fixed event or occurrence, as the date range between discrete start and end dates.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Frequency Pair
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A pair of frequencies for transmitting and receiving radio signals. The shore station transmits and receives on the frequencies indicated.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Position Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a position.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Light Sector
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Multiplicity of Features
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Online Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about online sources from which a resource or data can be obtained.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Periodic Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The active period of a recurring event or occurrence.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Wave Length
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distance between two successive peaks (or other points of identical phase) on an electromagnetic wave in the radar band of the electromagnetic spectrum.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Rhythm of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The sequence of times occupied by intervals of light/sound and eclipse/silence for all light characteristics or sound signals.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Schedule by Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The nature and timings of a daily schedule by days of the week.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Characteristics
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the characteristics of a light sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Additional textual information about a light sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Limit
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. The sector limit specifies the limits of the sector In a clockwise direction around the central feature (for example a light).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Limit One
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector limit one specifies the first limit of the sector. The order of sector limit one and sector limit two is clockwise around the central feature (for example a light).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Limit Two
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector limit two specifies the second limit of the sector. The order of sector limit one and sector limit two is clockwise around the central feature (for example a light).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Shape Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the shape of a non-standard topmark.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Sequence
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The sequence of times occupied by intervals of light/sound and eclipse/silence for all “light characteristics” or sound signals.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Spatial Accuracy
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides an indication of the vertical and horizontal positional uncertainty of bathymetric data, optionally within a specified date range.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunications
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A means or channel of communicating at a distance by electrical or electromagnetic means such as telegraphy, telephony, or broadcasting.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Tidal Stream Panel Values
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The direction of the flow and the tidal current rate from 6 hours before to 6 hours after high water (HW) or low water (LW) at the reference tide station, at hourly or sub-hourly intervals.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Tidal Stream Value
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the direction and speed of a tidal stream at a given time relative to the reference tide.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Time Intervals by Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The regular weekly operation times of a service or schedule.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Topmark
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A characteristic shape secured at the top of a buoy or beacon to aid in its identification.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Closed
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance of a feature in closed condition (for example a closed lifting bridge) measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance measured from the horizontal plane towards a fixed (non-opening) feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Open
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance of a feature in opened condition (for example an open lifting bridge) measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Safe
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The safe vertical clearance of a feature measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the vertical accuracy of depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The Collection
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to the aggregate in a whole-part relationship.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The Information
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to an object that provides more information about the referencing feature or information type.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The Equipment
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to the feature(s) supported by a structure feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The Structure
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to the feature that equipment feature(s) are supported by.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:name: Additional information
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:definition: A feature association for the binding between at least one instance of a geo feature and an instance of an information type.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:name: Aids to navigation association
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:definition: A feature association for the binding between navigational aids and the traffic systems (such as routeing measures) that they define.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:name: Structure/equipment
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:definition: A feature association for the binding between a navigation aid equipment feature and the structure that supports it.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Contact Details
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Information on how to reach a person or organisation by postal, internet, telephone, telex and radio systems.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Service Hours
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: The time when a service is available and known exceptions.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Non-Standard Working Day
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Days when many services are not available. Often days of festivity or recreation or public holidays when normal working hours are limited, especially a national or religious festival, etc.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Nautical Information
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Nautical information about a related area or facility.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Spatial Quality
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: The indication of the quality of the locational information for features in a dataset.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Aids to Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A visual, acoustical, or radio device, external to a ship, designed to assist in determining a safe course or a vessel's position, or to warn of dangers and/or obstructions. Aids to navigation usually include buoys, beacons, fog signals, lights, radio beacons, leading marks, radio position fixing systems and GNSS which are chart-related and assist safe navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light All Around
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An all around light is a light that is visible over the whole horizon of interest to marine navigation and having no change in the characteristics of the light.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Sectored
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A light presenting different appearances (in particular, different colours) over various parts of the horizon of interest to maritime navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Landmark
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Any prominent object at a fixed location on land which can be used in determining a location or a direction.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Air Obstruction
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An air obstruction light is a light marking an obstacle which constitutes a danger to air navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Cardinal Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A cardinal buoy is used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where the mariner may find the best navigable water. It is placed in one of the four quadrants (North, East, South and West), bounded by inter-cardinal bearings from the point marked.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Isolated Danger Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An isolated danger buoy is a buoy moored on or above an isolated danger of limited extent, which has navigable water all around it.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Safe Water Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A safe water buoy is used to indicate that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Special Purpose/General Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A special purpose buoy is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notices to Mariners.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Emergency Wreck Marking Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An emergency wreck marking buoy is a buoy moored on or above a new wreck, designed to provide a prominent (both visual and radio) and easily identifiable temporary first response.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Installation Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An installation buoy is a buoy used for loading tankers with gas or oil.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Mooring Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A buoy secured to the bottom by permanent moorings with means for mooring a vessel by use of its anchor chain or mooring lines.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Lateral Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A lateral beacon is used to indicate the port or starboard hand side of the route to be followed. They are generally used for well defined channels and are used in conjunction with a conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Cardinal Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A cardinal beacon is used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where the mariner may find the best navigable water. It is placed in one of the four quadrants (North, East, South and West), bounded by inter-cardinal bearings from the point marked.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Isolated Danger Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An isolated danger beacon is a beacon erected on an isolated danger of limited extent, which has navigable water all around it.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Safe Water Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A safe water beacon is used to indicate that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Special Purpose/General Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A special purpose beacon is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notices to Mariners.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Daymark
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: The identifying characteristics of an aid to navigation which serve to facilitate its recognition against a daylight viewing background. On those structures that do not by themselves present an adequate viewing area to be seen at the required distance, the aid is made more visible by affixing a daymark to the structure. A daymark so affixed has a distinctive colour and shape depending on the purpose of the aid.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Float
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A boat-like structure used instead of a light buoy in waters where strong streams or currents are experienced, or when a greater elevation than that of a light buoy is necessary.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Vessel
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A distinctively marked vessel anchored or moored at a charted point, to serve as an aid to navigation. By night, it displays a characteristic light(s) and is usually equipped with other devices, such as fog signal, submarine sound signal, and radio-beacon, to assist navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Retroreflector
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A means of distinguishing unlighted marks at night. Retroreflective material is secured to the mark in a particular pattern to reflect back light.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Radar Reflector
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A device capable of, or intended for, reflecting radar signals.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Fog Signal
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A warning signal transmitted by a vessel, or aid to navigation, during periods of low visibility. Also, the device producing such a signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Physical AIS Aid to Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An Automatic Identification System (AIS) message 21 transmitted from a physical Aid to Navigation, or transmitted from an AIS station for an Aid to Navigation which physically exists.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A transponder beacon transmitting a coded signal on radar frequency, permitting an interrogating craft to determine the bearing and range of the transponder.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Virtual AIS Aid to Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An Automatic Identification System (AIS) message 21 transmitted from an AIS station to simulate on navigation systems an Aid to Navigation which does not physically exist.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Lateral Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A lateral buoy is used to indicate the port or starboard hand side of the route to be followed. They are generally used for well-defined channels and are used in conjunction with a conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Fog Detector
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A fog detector light is a light used to automatically determine conditions of visibility which warrant the turning on or off of a sound signal.
